  "subject": "Retry CDS message correlation on DB deadlock",
  "commit_message": "Retry CDS message correlation on DB deadlock\n\nWhen multiple concurrent SO workflows compete for Camunda database\ntable locks, MariaDB may abort a transaction with a deadlock error.\nPreviously, this caused ControllerExecutionBB to fail permanently\nwith a misleading \"CANCELLED: Failed to read message\" error, even\nthough CDS had processed the request successfully.\n\nExtend tryCorrelateMessage() to catch DataAccessException and retry\nwhen the root cause is a SQLTransactionRollbackException (deadlock).\nThe existing retry loop (10 attempts, 1s apart) handles the backoff.\nNon-retryable data access exceptions are still re-thrown.\n\nIssue-ID: SO-4358\nChange-Id: Ie66c55b0a3a8963ff958a30b5933cce5013e9281\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\n",
